IF statements â€“ introduce you various IF statement to either execute or skip a sequence of statements based on a condition.

Example:

SET SERVEROUTPUT ON
DECLARE
num_small number(3):= &A;
num_large number(3):= &B;
num_temp number(3);
BEGIN
    IF(num_small > num_large) THEN 
        num_temp := num_small;
        num_small := num_large;
        num_large := num_temp;
        dbms_output.put_line('The smaller numer is '||num_small);
        dbms_output.put_line('The largeer numer is '||num_large);
    ELSE
        dbms_output.put_line('The smaller numer is '||num_small);
        dbms_output.put_line('The largeer numer is '||num_large);
    END IF;
END;
